Inception Score
Real Images 1.55 ±plus-or-minus\pm 0.04
Passive mGAN-AI 1.42 ±plus-or-minus\pm 0.02

references:
To quantitatively evaluate the generated images, the inception score [24] is used to statistically compare the three attack models. Inception score has been widely adopted in image quality evaluation, especially in the area of image synthesis.
We generate 400 samples from each of the three attacks and compute the inception score for each method. The results are shown in Table III, where the proposed mGAN-AI shows higher score than MI and GAN-based attack, demonstrating that mGAN-AI generates samples with higher quality.
